cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with the representation of planar graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of curves on a grid suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of 4-connectivity is related to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of a modification of a previous representation technique suggests a possible connection to software engineering and programming (cs.SI).
